How to Use

Launch the application
Enter the amount you want to convert
Select the source currency (From)
Select the target currency (To)
Click "Convert" to see the result

Example:

Amount: 100
From: USD
To: EUR
Result: 100.00 USD = 85.23 EUR

Dependencies

JavaFX 21.0.1 - UI framework
Gson 2.10.1 - JSON parsing
Java HTTP Client - API requests (built-in)

API Information
This app uses ExchangeRate-API v6:

Endpoint: https://v6.exchangerate-api.com/v6/{API_KEY}/latest/{CURRENCY}
Free tier: 1,500 requests per month
Documentation: https://www.exchangerate-api.com/docs

Testing with Boomerang API
You can test the API integration using Boomerang:

Install Boomerang Chrome extension
Test the endpoint:

   GET https://v6.exchangerate-api.com/v6/YOUR_API_KEY/latest/USD

Verify you get a 200 OK response with exchange rate data

Common Issues & Solutions
Problem: "Cannot resolve symbol JavaFX"
Solution:

Make sure JavaFX is in your pom.xml dependencies
Reload Maven project: Right-click â†’ Maven â†’ Reload Project

Problem: "Module not found: javafx.controls"
Solution:

Add VM options: --module-path PATH_TO_FX --add-modules javafx.controls
Or set in IDE run configuration

Problem: API returns 401 Unauthorized
Solution:

Check that you've added your actual API key
Verify the key is active on exchangerate-api.com

Problem: "Connection refused" or timeout
Solution:

Check your internet connection
Verify the API endpoint URL is correct
Check if you've exceeded your monthly request limit

